text: The Collegium Carolinum (also known as ) was a scientific institution in Kassel. It was founded in 1709 by Charles I, Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel. It was closed after the death of Frederick II, Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel in 1785. == Notable professors == * Georg Forster, naturalist * Johann Heinrich Tischbein, painter == References == Category:1709 establishments Category:1780s disestablishments Category:Colleges and universities in Hesse Category:Education in Hesse Category:Kassel
